dismissalText.commentary: Dinesh Chandimal st †Dhoni b Ashwin 64 (81b 4x4 0x6 98m) SR: 79.01

dismissalComment.html: Dhoni has done well to complete the stumping, Chandimal walked out, reached the tossed up carrom ball on the full, but missed, and it turned away sharply from him after pitching outside leg, and thudded into Dhoni's gloves hard just outside off, Dhoni was startled for a bit, but with Chandimal way down the track, he got the bails off eventually

dismissalText.commentary: Tillakaratne Dilshan c Kohli b Jadeja 48 (79b 6x4 0x6 102m) SR: 60.75

dismissalComment.html: Virat gets the chance to make up for that wide throw and does superbly to hold on to a very low catch at point, he pouches it and screams, Dilshan was looking to cut almost everything from Jadeja and could not keep this very wide one down

gone! Mahela departs, sweeps from off straight to deep square leg, well judged low take from Rohit on the boundary, Mahela had moved across and fetched it from around off stump, was a bit off balance as he played the shot

Ashwin gets another one, Perera advanced out to have a heave, was beaten as the tossed up ball spun away, he got the foot back on the crease, but could not get it behind the line as Dhoni removed the bails

dismissalText.commentary: Virat Kohli run out (Malinga) 77 (94b 8x4 1x6 156m) SR: 81.91

dismissalComment.html: Virat is down on the ground in pain, he might be gone too, a risky single it was going to be as he pushed to mid on and set off, a direct hit, and he is gone by miles, he is writhing in pain, but he will have to get up and walk back, needless single, it was the last ball of the over, did that have something to do with it? He is being helped off the ground now

commentTextItems.html: three men, one ball, and none could catch it, they stood and watched, Ashwin wanted to finish it  with a loft over mid off, mistimed it, the ball looped up wide of mid off, there were three men converging on it, each thought one of the other two would get to it, and none did, Ashwin smiles broadly as he completes the single

commentPostTextItems.html: That is it from us for this game. Have a look at Nitin Sundar's match report. Abhishek Purohit signing off for the moment, Cheers.

Dhoni: "I always smile whether we are winning or losing, it is good to be on the winning side. Ashwin had to bowl out of his comfort zone in the Powerplays and the slog overs. He did well and batted well. We have confidence in Jadeja to bat at No 7 and bowl well. You have to be ready for these circumstances [Virat's cramping], you have to hydrate yourself well, you do not get a runner nowadays. People commit mistakes, it happens."

R Ashwin is Man of the Match. Ashwin: "It was gripping a little bit, I got a few wickets and at the end, finished it off with the bat. One victory on the board is very important, I was desperate to get a win today. i would rather rate myself to unfold as the game goes on, will like to be considered as an offie first. I told Jaddu that we have to bat 60 balls here and that is what we did."

Mahela: "We were probably 30-40 runs short. We had our chances but they played better than us. We kept wickets in hand, we did not play their spinners well, we got bogged down in the middle period. We need to get runs on the board."

Turned out to be a comfortable win in the end. Sri Lanka did not attack enough after they had India at 181 for 6, and Ashwin and Jadeja were calm enough to guide them home. Ashwin's game all the way, brilliant with ball, cool with the bat
zakaria: "Ashwin's batting is so unSehwagisc. Just love it."
Dinesh: "Still disappointed with India .They didnt learn from the test series.Lot of batsmen got good starts but none converted it to a big score."

commentPreTextItems.html: jose: "Sensible batting by this pair. That was all what was needed."

commentTextItems.html: ho ho, he shows the specialist batsmen how it is done, he steps outside his crease, takes on the short ball and clatters it to the deep midwicket boundary, again, completely in control
works through midwicket for a single
surprised as he this one bounces from a good length, and somehow jabs it down the track
he even pulls, he gets four, he can't do anything wrong today, a short-arm pull, in the air, and down to the deep midwicket boundary, no desperation at all against the short ball, not even a hint
pushes harder this time but mid off gets around to it
he has time to get across and push the length delivery to mid on
pushed off the front foot, bowler gets a hand to it and parries it to mid off
pushed to extra cover
charges out and smashes the full delivery to sweeper cover

shot! that has gone all the way to the boundary, some timing from Ashwin, leans forward to a widish length delivery and times the push in the gap between extra cover and mid off, who ends up chasing it into the boundary
there comes the short ball, but Ashwin does well to drop his wrists and allows it to scream past
tries one more yorker, this ends as a very low full toss around leg stump, worked through midwicket
goes for the yorker, not quite in the blockhole, squeezed out to point
goes for the full delivery on the stumps, Ashwin flicks in the air through midwicket

commentPreTextItems.html: Chris: "This partnership proves 2 things- Sri Lankan cricket is in shambles. And India's best batsmen are the bowlers!"

commentTextItems.html: starts off with a length ball, dabbed to point
driven off the front foot through point, the throw comes in from the deep, but Jadeja has made his ground comfortably
that is quite well played, waits for the length ball to arrive, and whips it from the crease in front of square leg
tries to run this one down to third man but point gets to it
shortish, wide, cracked to sweeper cover

dismissalText.commentary: Dinesh Chandimal st †Dhoni b Ashwin 64 (81b 4x4 0x6 98m) SR: 79.01

dismissalComment.html: Dhoni has done well to complete the stumping, Chandimal walked out, reached the tossed up carrom ball on the full, but missed, and it turned away sharply from him after pitching outside leg, and thudded into Dhoni's gloves hard just outside off, Dhoni was startled for a bit, but with Chandimal way down the track, he got the bails off eventually

dismissalText.commentary: Lahiru Thirimanne run out (Sharma/†Dhoni) 7 (11b 0x4 0x6 9m) SR: 63.63

dismissalComment.html: run out by a mile and more to spare, it was guided straight to backward point, there was no single, Thirimanne wanted it, was stranded halfway down the pitch and had no chance of getting back as the throw came in to the keeper

dismissalText.commentary: Nuwan Kulasekara c Sharma b Vinay Kumar 7 (9b 0x4 0x6 18m) SR: 77.77

dismissalComment.html: Kula backs away and has a slog, the edge flies vertically behind point, Rohit sets himself under it, and scrambles to take it safely as it eventually comes down

headshotImage.longCaption: Virender Sehwag player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Virender Sehwag c Kulasekara b Malinga 10 (8b 2x4 0x6 12m) SR: 125

dismissalComment.html: oh well, Sehwag gives it away, short and wide from Malinga, Sehwag hops and forces it over the in-field, but third man is around and he runs to his right to gleefully hold on

headshotImage.caption: Angelo Mathews, player page headshot cutout 2023
headshotImage.longCaption: Angelo Mathews, player page headshot cutout 2023

dismissalText.commentary: Sachin Tendulkar b Mathews 48 (63b 5x4 0x6 87m) SR: 76.19

dismissalComment.html: oh dear, Sachin has played on, he had earlier tried to steer Angelo from the middle and leg line, tried to back away again to one angled in and run it to third man from very close to off stump, and this time he chopped it on

dismissalText.commentary: Virat Kohli run out (Malinga) 77 (94b 8x4 1x6 156m) SR: 81.91

dismissalComment.html: Virat is down on the ground in pain, he might be gone too, a risky single it was going to be as he pushed to mid on and set off, a direct hit, and he is gone by miles, he is writhing in pain, but he will have to get up and walk back, needless single, it was the last ball of the over, did that have something to do with it? He is being helped off the ground now

dismissalText.commentary: Rohit Sharma c Dilshan b Perera 10 (17b 1x4 0x6 29m) SR: 58.82

dismissalComment.html: Super Dilshan grabs the screamer at point, short, wide, Rohit cracks the cut, does not bother to keep it down, it flies to Dilshan's left, he may be former captain but is still a top fielder, he reacts immediately, bends low to his left, pouches the ball safely and tumbles down only to be engulfed by his team-mates as he gets up

headshotImage.caption: Angelo Mathews, player page headshot cutout 2023
headshotImage.longCaption: Angelo Mathews, player page headshot cutout 2023

dismissalText.commentary: Suresh Raina c sub (SMSM Senanayake) b Mathews 24 (27b 3x4 0x6 30m) SR: 88.88

dismissalComment.html: well, he has indeed fallen to the short ball ultimately, it was nowhere as sharp as the short balls Malinga aimed at his ribs, it was angled across him, the pull was on, Raina went at it too eagerly, and it ballooned up high to settle into the hands of deep midwicket

seriesStandings.notes:
Preliminary Matches Win, with bonus point - 5
Win, without bonus point - 4
Tie or No Result - 2
Loss - 0 In the event of teams finishing on equal points, the right to play in the final match or series will be determined as follows:
  • The team with the most number of wins
  • If still equal, the team with the most number of wins over the other team(s) who are equal on points and have the same number of wins
  • If still equal, the team with the highest number of bonus points
  • If still equal, the team with the highest net run rate
In a match declared as no result, run rate is not applicable. Net Run Rate A team's net run rate is calculated by deducting from the average runs per over scored by that team throughout the competition, the average runs per over scored against that team throughout the competition. In the event of a team being all out in less than its full quota of overs, the calculation of its net run rate shall be based on the full quota of overs to which it would have been entitled and not on the number of overs in which the team was dismissed. Only those matches where results are achieved will count for the purpose of net run rate calculations. Where a match is abandoned, but a result is achieved under Duckworth/Lewis, for net run rate purposes Team 1 will be accredited with Team 2's Par Score on abandonment off the same number of overs faced by Team 2. Where a match is concluded but with Duckworth/Lewis having been applied at an earlier point in the match, Team 1 will be accredited with 1 run less than the final Target Score for Team 2 off the total number of overs allocated to Team 2 to reach the target. Bonus Points The team that achieves a run rate of 1.25 times that of the opposition shall be awarded one bonus point. A team's run rate will be calculated by reference to the runs scored in an innings divided by the number of overs faced.
